    <briefdescription>
<para>Semantic, driver-agnostic storage interface for the SQL catalog. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A store instance is scoped to one catalog name and persists namespace and table rows. Implementations must be safe for concurrent calls from <computeroutput><ref refid="classiceberg_1_1sql_1_1SqlCatalog" kindref="compound">SqlCatalog</ref></computeroutput>.</para>
<para>Unique or primary-key constraint violations from insert and rename operations must be reported as <computeroutput>ErrorKind::kAlreadyExists</computeroutput>. Other database failures should be reported as <computeroutput>ErrorKind::kIOError</computeroutput>. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
